Linux Recover Boot Loader
------------------------------
BIOS [ basic input output system ] - motherboard se jitne bhi component connected hai , usme power proper mil pa rha hai ya nhi mil pa rha hai, saren component ko proper power mil pa rha hai toh , next process me jata hai 

Boot Loder : operating system ko RAM me load krna hota hai , tabhi jakar aapka Operating System ON hota hai ,
linux me jo boot loader hai wo grub hai 

GRUB    ------- abhi present me jo version chal rha hai wo GRUB2 hai 

GRUB ek progrm hai jisme ye mentioned hai kaise load krna hai operating system ko.



Check for EFI firmware directory

ls /sys/firmware/efi

- If the directory exists and lists files → UEFI system.
- If you get No such file or directory → Legacy BIOS system.

cd /boot/grub2
rm -rf grub.cfg
reboot

Now error will show on terminal
-----------------------------------

grub>


Now my challange is , to recover this

so jo bhi image isme load thi usko lena hai , ya pendrive me ho ya dvd me ho
